This course section is about staying clean.

2
00:00:05,610 --> 00:00:07,950
I want to ensure that you're really able

3
00:00:07,950 --> 00:00:09,450
to apply what you learned

4
00:00:09,450 --> 00:00:13,170
and that you can take the next step and write better code

5
00:00:13,170 --> 00:00:15,280
than you maybe did before.

6
00:00:15,280 --> 00:00:17,280
And for that, the most important rule,

7
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:18,609
which you must not forget.

8
00:00:18,609 --> 00:00:23,609
Clean code is equal to readable and understandable code.

9
00:00:24,150 --> 00:00:26,310
Whatever helps this goal.

10
00:00:26,310 --> 00:00:29,500
So whenever you do something which improves readability

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:33,570
and understandability, it makes your code cleaner.

12
00:00:33,570 --> 00:00:35,670
This is really important to keep in mind.

13
00:00:35,670 --> 00:00:38,920
It's not about checking 10 different rules

14
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,890
which you apply to your code.

15
00:00:40,890 --> 00:00:45,030
It is about writing readable and understandable code.

16
00:00:45,030 --> 00:00:47,030
That is the ultimate goal.

17
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:48,630
Don't forget this.

18
00:00:48,630 --> 00:00:51,670
Also, don't forget that whilst we didn't focus

19
00:00:51,670 --> 00:00:54,740
on a specific programming paradigm or style

20
00:00:54,740 --> 00:00:56,323
or language in this course,

21
00:00:56,323 --> 00:00:58,940
the rules and concepts taught in this course

22
00:00:58,940 --> 00:01:00,430
will always apply.

23
00:01:00,430 --> 00:01:03,380
You always want to have readable and meaningful names.

24
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:05,720
You always want to have slim, concise

25
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:06,990
and clean functions.

26
00:01:06,990 --> 00:01:10,100
And you always want to have an understandable control flow

27
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:12,270
and no nested if statements.

28
00:01:12,270 --> 00:01:15,340
So this all always applies.

29
